  Actually, you're wrong.  There is quite a bit of useless crap in the druid class that most druids wouldn't mind losing at all.  Spells that only effect summoned mobs anyone?  Treeform which hasn't worked since Luclin's release (oh, but thanks for the new treeform spell in PoP, SOE you dumbfucks).  Wolf form which stacks with about nothing and doesn't work indoors.  Strength buffs which are nearly useless.  PoP has also rendered regen nearly useless and it's loss wouldn't be missed, damage shields are right up there too as mages will do them on raids and an extra 40 damage in a group against a mob hitting for 600+ isn't going to add a lot.  Also there are &quot;fun&quot; spells which are basically useless although druids probably wouldn't want to give them up, bearpet, rain stopping and plant charming for instance.  Then there are the completely redundant spells.  Why are there evacs to zones that druids can just port to, and porting to Misty Thicket (a clicky effect on velious legs and luclin quest earring) is pretty redundant with the book sitting right beside the ring.<br>
